FBIS4-12062 "drnes065_l_94013" FBIS-NES-94-065 Daily Report 4 Apr 1994 ISRAEL IDF To Be Responsible for Palestinian Policemen IDF To Be Responsible for Palestinian Policemen TA0404193294 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network in Hebrew 1700 GMT 4 Apr 94 TA0404193294 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network in Hebrew 1700 GMT 4 Apr 94 Hebrew BFN [Excerpt] As of tomorrow, the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] units in the Gaza Strip will start operating on the basis of new directives especially formulated for the interim period. Our military affairs correspondent Alon Ben-David has learned that tomorrow the IDF forces will start the overlapping with the first Palestinian policemen. According to the new directives, the IDF will be responsible for the safety of the policemen. Soldiers are forbidden to open fire at suspicious vehicles or cars which run over roadblocks unless it is clear that it is a terrorist attack. [passage omitted]
